claim: Flublok contains 45 micrograms (mcg) of HA per strain vs 15 mcg of HA per strain in a standard-dose influenza vaccine.
explanation: Flowchart showing the selection and breakdown of a study cohort of adults aged ≥18 years (N=18,467) into analyzable cohort (N=15,203), then into controls (N=13,385) and influenza cases (N=1,868), with subsequent classification of participants by vaccine type: recombinant quadrivalent influenza vaccine (RIV4), standard-dose quadrivalent influenza vaccine (SD-IIV4), high-dose quadrivalent influenza vaccine plus adjuvanted influenza vaccine (HD-IIV4 + Adj-IIV), and unvaccinated. The figure does not present any information about hemagglutinin (HA) microgram content per strain for Flublok (RIV4) or standard-dose vaccines, so it does not support the claim. Note: The image is clear and legible, but no dosing information is included; confidence in this determination is high.
